message.content:
To get to the grocery store that is 1km away in Slovenia, you have a few options:

1. Walking: If the weather is pleasant and you enjoy walking, you can simply walk to the grocery store. It will take you approximately 10-15 minutes to cover a distance of 1km.

2. Cycling: Slovenia is known for its cycling-friendly infrastructure, so if you have a bicycle, you can ride to the grocery store. It will be a quick and convenient way to reach your destination.

3. Public transportation: Check if there are any bus stops near your location and the grocery store. You can use public transportation to reach the store. Look for bus schedules and routes to plan your journey accordingly.

4. Car: If you have access to a car or can use a ride-sharing service, driving to the grocery store is another option. It will be the fastest way to reach your destination, especially if you have heavy groceries to carry back.

Consider the factors like weather, convenience, and your personal preferences to choose the best mode of transportation for your trip to the grocery store.
